The paper proposes a new approach for multi-choice reading comprehension, which involves natural language processing and machine learning techniques. The most relevant arXiv CS sub-category is likely to be cs.CL (Computation and Language), which covers topics related to natural language processing and computational linguistics. Other relevant sub-categories include cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence), cs.LG (Machine Learning), cs.IR (Information Retrieval), and cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing), which also involve machine learning and computational techniques.
